an Quartet", "qid": null, "roles": ["jazz_ensemble"]}]}, {"label": "I'm a Ding Dong Daddy", "work": "I'm a Ding Dong Daddy", "composer": "Phil Baxter", "performers": []}, {"label": "Sing, Sing, Sing", "work": "Sing, Sing, Sing", "composer": "Louis Prima", "performers": []}, {"label": "Big John Special", "work": "Big John Special", "composer": "Fletcher Henderson", "performers": []}, {"label": "Selections (unspecified)", "work": "Selections (unspecified)", "composer": null, "performers": [{"id": "4306", "name": "Vernon Brown", "qid": "Q2517328", "roles": ["trombone"]}, {"id": "9061", "name": "Babe Rusin", "qid": null, "roles": ["woodwinds"]}, {"id": "9062", "name": "George Koenig", "qid": "Q55862615", "roles": ["woodwinds"]}, {"id": "11443", "name": "Harry Goodman", "qid": "Q109123293", "roles": ["double_bass"]}, {"id": "14016", "name": "Chris Griffin", "qid": "Q1077247", "roles": ["trumpet"]}, {"id": "17368", "name": "Martha Tilton", "qid": "Q276227", "roles": ["vocalist"]}, {"id": "21591", "name": "Johnny Hodges", "qid": "Q455176", "roles": ["soprano_saxophone"]}, {"id": "23735", "name": "Hymie Schertzer", "qid": "Q1640653", "roles": ["woodwinds"]}, {"id": "28036", "name": "Ziggy Elman", "qid": "Q199406", "roles": ["trumpet"]}, {"id": "38780", "name": "Red Ballard", "qid": null, "roles": ["trombone"]}, {"id": "39228", "name": "Allan Reuss", "qid": "Q961314", "roles": ["guitar"]}, {"id": "45679", "name": "Harry James", "qid": "Q163861", "roles": ["trumpet"]}, {"id": "49662", "name": "Bobby Hackett", "qid": "Q578302", "roles": ["cornet"]}, {"id": "53346", "name": "Arthur Rollini", "qid": "Q711182", "roles": ["woodwinds"]}, {"id": "58023", "name": "Jess Stacy", "qid": "Q1688123", "roles": ["piano"]}, {"id": "58026", "name": "Cootie Williams", "qid": "Q523899", "roles": ["trumpet"]}]}], "quotes": [{"speaker": "Count Basie", "qid": "Q107008", "text": "Yes, I remember it very well. It was a great concert, and that was my first time at Carnegie Hall onstage. John had once taken me to hear Marion Anderson, which is something I will never forget.", "caption": "Count Basie recalls his first Carnegie Hall performance in 1938", "conf": "high", "first_person": true, "doc_title": "52157_Count Basie oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/52157/"}, {"speaker": "Count Basie", "qid": "Q107008", "text": "Yeah, I know that was the first time I had ever been on the stage at Carnegie Hall.", "caption": "Recalling his first Carnegie Hall performance in 1938", "conf": "high", "first_person": null, "doc_title": "52157_Count Basie oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/52157/"}, {"speaker": "Count Basie", "qid": "Q107008", "text": "Oh, you've heard it. But that was a great time, the concert with Bennie, and the thrill of just being and working at Carnegie Hall -- it sort of gave you goose pimples, you know. (Inaudible) My fingers were kinda damp when I started to play.", "caption": "Basie recalls playing with Benny Goodman at Carnegie Hall", "conf": "high", "first_person": true, "doc_title": "52157_Count Basie oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/52157/"}, {"speaker": "Teddy Wilson", "qid": "Q506052", "text": "And then the next important part in the movie, I guess, they have us doing -- oh, after the band -- that's because the band leader in certain scenes where we're playing at the Palomar Ballroom in Los Angeles, I guess, and the success of the band, and all of a sudden, after flopping along the line, then the tremendous success. And then, of course, the movie ends with the Carnegie Hall Concert in 1938, with the tremendous triumph of the band, the first all jazz concert in Carnegie Hall.", "caption": "Recalling the historic 1938 Benny Goodman concert", "conf": "high", "first_person": null, "doc_title": "66600_Teddy Wilson oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/66600/"}, {"speaker": "Buck Clayton", "qid": "Q999321", "text": "Well that was my first time ever to play Carnegie Hall and it was the time that", "caption": "Buck Clayton recalls his first Carnegie Hall performance", "conf": "low", "first_person": true, "doc_title": "67246_Buck Clayton oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/67246/"}], "featured_people": [{"qid": "Q961314", "id": "39228", "name": "Allan Reuss"}, {"qid": "Q711182", "id": "53346", "name": "Arthur Rollini"}, {"qid": "Q46755", "id": "30156", "name": "Benny Goodman"}, {"qid": "Q578302", "id": "49662", "name": "Bobby Hackett"}, {"qid": "Q999321", "id": "58121", "name": "Buck Clayton"}, {"qid": "Q1077247", "id": "14016", "name": "Chris Griffin"}, {"qid": "Q523899", "id": "58026", "name": "Cootie Williams"}, {"qid": "Q107008", "id": "31322", "name": "Count Basie"}, {"qid": "Q722441", "id": "22610", "name": "Freddie Green"}, {"qid": "Q319980", "id": "40453", "name": "Gene Krupa"}, {"qid": "Q55862615", "id": "9062", "name": "George Koenig"}, {"qid": "Q1375567", "id": "29100", "name": "Harry Carney"}, {"qid": "Q109123293", "id": "11443", "name": "Harry Goodman"}, {"qid": "Q163861", "id": "45679", "name": "Harry James"}, {"qid": "Q1640653", "id": "23735", "name": "Hymie Schertzer"}, {"qid": "Q1688123", "id": "58023", "name": "Jess Stacy"}, {"qid": "Q455176", "id": "21591", "name": "Johnny Hodges"}, {"qid": "Q110714", "id": "7569", "name": "Lester Young"}, {"qid": "Q313525", "id": "41532", "name": "Lionel Hampton"}, {"qid": "Q276227", "id": "17368", "name": "Martha Tilton"}, {"qid": "Q506052", "id": "1195", "name": "Teddy Wilson"}, {"qid": "Q2517328", "id": "4306", "name": "Vernon Brown"}, {"qid": "Q1382200", "id": "4878", "name": "Walter Page"}, {"qid": "Q199406", "id": "28036", "name": "Ziggy Elman"}]}